The paper discusses a scheduling scheme for data collection in LoRaWAN, which is a wireless network technology for low-power, wide-area IoT devices. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and specifically addresses the scalability issue of LoRaWAN, which is a common problem in network protocols (cs.CR). The proposed scheme involves allocating resources and scheduling transmissions, which involves system-level control (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of spreading factors and frequency channels, which are related to signal processing and information theory (cs.IT).
